## 4. AWS MIGRATION READINESS — design rules

These rules exist so that the future migration to AWS is as painless as possible:

| What changes on AWS | Where it is isolated now | What is NOT touched |
|---|---|---|
| Chatbot logic → AWS AI (Bedrock / Lambda) | `chat_service.py` | Router, frontend, DB |
| Email → AWS SES | `email_service.py` (new `SESEmailProvider`) | Everything else |
| Background jobs → AWS EventBridge + Lambda | `workers/tasks.py` | Everything else |
| Deployment → AWS ECS / Fargate | `docker-compose.yml` → `Dockerfile` | Application code |
| Database → AWS RDS PostgreSQL | Connection string in `.env` | Models and migrations |

**Concrete rules:**
- Never use local file paths to store data — everything goes to the database or environment variables
- Never use server-side sessions — only JWT in the Authorization header
- All environment-specific values in `.env` — never if/else on hostname in code
- Docker containers must be stateless — restarting a container must not affect user data

