## 5. WHAT IS MVP — implement first

MVP is defined as: **a student can book a consultation through the chatbot, and a professor can view and manage those bookings.**

### MVP — MUST work

**Auth (all roles)**
- [ ] Login with email + password
- [ ] OTP flow on first login (forced password change)
- [ ] JWT protection on all routes, role-based access

**Admin**
- [ ] Create accounts (student, professor) with OTP generation
- [ ] Enter exam period (date_from, date_to)
- [ ] Enter midterms and exams (course, date, type)
- [ ] Enter courses and student enrollments

**Professor**
- [ ] Define weekly consultation windows (day, time_from, time_to, type: REGULAR | THESIS)
- [ ] Block specific dates
- [ ] View registered students per slot (grouped by task, anonymous question visible)
- [ ] Mark a slot as completed or no-show

**Student — chatbot**
- [ ] Free-form first message → parser extracts professor, type, course, task, group size, urgency
- [ ] Follow-up questions until all required fields are filled (one at a time)
- [ ] Manual dropdown fallback after 2 failed parse attempts
- [ ] Show available slots as chip buttons
- [ ] Confirm booking → create `Booking` record
- [ ] Cancel a booking through chat

**Student — direct (without chatbot)**
- [ ] View my bookings (upcoming + past)
- [ ] Browse professors with profiles and `pinned_note`

**Notifications (in-app)**
- [ ] Create a notification on every significant action (confirmed, cancelled, no-show)
- [ ] Display in UI with 60-second polling
- [ ] Mark as read

---

### POST-MVP — implement if time allows

These features **do not block** the app from working. Database tables and API routes for them must exist (to avoid future migrations), but UI and business logic can be stubs.

**Scheduler (APScheduler tasks)**
- [ ] 7 days before exam — notify professor for preparation session + auto-escalation
- [ ] Reminders 24h and 1h before slot
- [ ] Feedback trigger 2h after slot ends
- [ ] Waitlist check on cancellation (with 2h confirmation window)
- [ ] Cancellation penalty detection
- [ ] Scheduler log view in admin panel + manual trigger button

**Thesis flow**
- [ ] Student applies for thesis supervision (form + pending status)
- [ ] Professor accepts/rejects from inbox
- [ ] Student sees thesis slots only after being accepted

**Waitlist**
- [ ] Join waitlist when a slot is full
- [ ] Notify when a spot opens
- [ ] Appeal penalty

**Dashboard and analytics**
- [ ] Professor stats (total, by type, no-show rate, avg feedback)
- [ ] Predictive model (previous year's data)
- [ ] Admin global dashboard

**Email notifications**
- [ ] Booking confirmation
- [ ] Reminder emails
- [ ] Waitlist notification

**Other**
- [ ] Post-consultation feedback form (rating + comment)
- [ ] System config editor for admin
- [ ] Privacy page + consent modal
- [ ] Announcements (admin → all students)
- [ ] FAQ knowledge base (admin editor + chatbot integration)
- [ ] One-off extra slots outside regular windows

